Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.51,0:01:51.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It should be somewhere\Naround here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.58,0:01:56.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't hurry, the poison mist that\Nyesterday's downpour cleared away...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.91,0:01:59.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...will return to the valley floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.02,0:02:04.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Highness, I shall return\Nwith proof that Prince Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.39,0:02:06.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is still alive without fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.90,0:02:20.90,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 16\NWith All One's Heart
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.65,0:02:31.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.75,0:02:36.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the time being, we can't let anyone\Noutside the palace know of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.02,0:02:41.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When the time is right, I promise\Nthat the entire country will mourn him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.22,0:02:43.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, please endure your grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.52,0:03:14.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without the mikado, everyone\Nis distracted and unfocused.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.12,0:03:19.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this state of affairs continues,\Nthe government will cease to function.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:24.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And our one faint\Nglimmer of hope is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.92,0:03:41.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you men doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.39,0:03:49.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The master star reader\Nhas known all along...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.96,0:03:55.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that you won the trust of the vessels\Nand entered the chamber of epitaphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:59.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are here on orders of\Nthe master star reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:03.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I assume that you\Nhave come here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.14,0:04:07.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...because you believe that\NPrince Chagum is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:10.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But just how much faith do\Nyou have in your deductions?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:14.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the course of reading the epitaphs,\Nmy hope changed to certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.55,0:04:21.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this so-called certainty of yours\Nshould prove to be mistaken...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:25.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I must warn you that\Nyou will die with this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.19,0:04:28.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and your corpses will be\Nlost forever in this valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.85,0:04:52.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The poison mist has receded.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.37,0:05:42.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only I had gone down\Nto the valley floor that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.54,0:05:47.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I found there was the corpse of\Ntheir Kokkou stallion and their clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:51.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There was no sign of the corpses\Nof the prince and the bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.15,0:05:56.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't stopped you,\Nwe would have...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:06:00.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There was enough poison mist\Nthat day to kill even me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.56,0:06:02.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You made the correct decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.36,0:06:06.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The odds of the prince being\Nalive are now much higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.73,0:06:09.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The question now\Nis how to find him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.93,0:06:12.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you given the\Nmatter any thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.50,0:06:14.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.01,0:06:20.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make haste\Nback to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.01,0:06:24.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We must first report this to the\Nmikado and the master star reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.28,0:06:29.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Sagum will be\Noverjoyed at this news as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.73,0:06:38.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.63,0:06:42.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Brace yourself for what\NI am about to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.99,0:07:11.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only I had told him that Prince Chagum\Nwas alive when I had the chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.41,0:07:30.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Star Reader,\Nas you are already aware...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.41,0:07:34.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I have been infiltrating the secret\Nrepository and reading the epitaphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.95,0:07:38.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And in doing so, I discovered\Na fact of utmost importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.56,0:07:44.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The legends set down in the official history\Nregarding the founding of Shin-Yogo...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.79,0:07:46.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...contain grave errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.30,0:07:52.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The official history\Nis nothing but a story...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.64,0:07:55.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a fabrication designed\Nto control the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.74,0:08:01.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the water demon was in fact\Na water spirit that spews forth clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.41,0:08:03.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...bringing bounty to our land.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:08.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I find your story difficult to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.75,0:08:12.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Long before the arrival of\NEmperor Torugaru, our founding father...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.52,0:08:15.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the Yakoo, the original\Ninhabitants of this land...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.83,0:08:20.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...were aware of the existence of\NNayug, a world other than our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:24.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They understood that\Nour bounty is caused by...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:26.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a spirit that\Ndwells between worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.27,0:08:30.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kainan Nanai sensed\Nthis as a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.44,0:08:33.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By creating a new\Nmyth for the public...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.31,0:08:35.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he eradicated the\NYakoo's oral traditions...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.48,0:08:39.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and laid the foundation\Nfor the Shin-Yogo Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.55,0:08:43.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, aware of the danger\Nof letting the fateful day arrive...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.59,0:08:45.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...having armed us only\Nwith the incorrect oral history...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.79,0:08:49.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He built the epitaph chamber\Nin order to entrust us with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.59,0:08:54.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On one of those stone tablets kept\Nunderground, the following was inscribed:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.90,0:08:58.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Those who serve as star readers must\Nread and decipher what is written here..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.77,0:09:02.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"...to prepare for the natural disaster\Nwhich will come every hundred years..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.51,0:09:08.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"...passing down the knowledge\Nto each successive generation."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.15,0:09:13.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is happening now is\Nexactly as you said, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.08,0:09:15.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We brought this emergency\Ndown on ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.99,0:09:19.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...as the result of us star readers\Nbecoming preoccupied with politics!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:24.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As proof of this, by studying\Nthe events set forth in the epitaphs...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.59,0:09:28.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I am now almost certain\Nthat Prince Chagum is still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.93,0:09:32.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The prince still carries\Nthe spirit's egg within him...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.30,0:09:35.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and he is living somewhere\Nin Kosenkyo as we speak!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.24,0:09:43.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the being inside the prince is\Nindeed a spirit that creates water...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.75,0:09:47.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...how do you explain the sign of\Nthe great drought not disappearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.99,0:09:53.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The sign of the drought\Nthat we see now is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:58.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a preordained sign that occurs\Nwhen the spirit is about to be reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.46,0:10:05.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Had the prince been assassinated,\Nnot only would there have been no rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:09.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but I expect these lands would\Nnever have had another drop of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:12.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:16.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is what you just said true?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.85,0:10:21.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I am convinced of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:26.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are certain that\NChagum is alive, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.76,0:10:27.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.29,0:10:33.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Although I have not seen him with\Nmy own eyes, there can be no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.73,0:10:37.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.87,0:10:43.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I were to be given command\Nof the search for Prince Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.64,0:10:47.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I shall find him\Nin a matter of days!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.38,0:10:52.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mikado...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.22,0:10:56.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would appear that\NI was even more obsessed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.49,0:10:59.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...with political matters\Nthan I realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.29,0:11:04.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is but one thing\Nthat I can do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.13,0:11:10.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sire, please grant Shuga full command\Nover the search for Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.67,0:11:14.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you on his behalf. Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:19.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Do as you see fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.78,0:11:21.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.48,0:11:28.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sire, there is something that I must\Nask to borrow to carry out the search.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.32,0:11:32.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you wish the use of?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.81,0:11:51.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here, have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.37,0:11:52.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:57.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like business is booming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.45,0:11:58.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.62,0:12:01.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you, Tanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.65,0:12:05.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that any way to welcome me?\NI'm here as a customer today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.89,0:12:12.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to deliver these\Ngoods to this address here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.49,0:12:15.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If at all possible, today\Nor tomorrow. Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.83,0:12:23.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think you're talking to?\NI'm the best errand runner in this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.91,0:12:27.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I forgot.\NThere won't be any problems, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.24,0:12:28.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave you to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.38,0:12:33.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.32,0:12:37.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to launch our plan soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.09,0:12:40.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your men may start whenever\Nyou think the timing is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.03,0:12:55.04,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.64,0:12:58.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can gather these\Nsupplies for you today...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.57,0:13:03.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but from the looks of this order,\Nis Balsa planning another long trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.18,0:13:05.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:11.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll make sure that\Nno one knows about the delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.55,0:13:15.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the money she\Ntold me to give to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:18.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't take Balsa's money!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.86,0:13:23.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's thanks to her that Saya\Nand I have our own shop now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:26.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly, she did tell us\Nthat we shouldn't use it yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.84,0:13:31.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let us do something to repay her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:33.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.34,0:13:36.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.38,0:13:38.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's more like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:40.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.48,0:13:42.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing! Leave everything to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.15,0:13:44.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure doing business with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.46,0:13:51.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Chief! What brings\Nyou here at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.29,0:13:56.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we've been hired to do\Na major renovation on a mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.77,0:13:58.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying to get everything ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.07,0:14:04.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to buy a lot of cypress wood.\NAs I recall, you also deal in lumber, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.64,0:14:06.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You bet we do!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.54,0:14:11.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That "Errand Runner" sign isn't\Njust there for show, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.31,0:14:13.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's discuss\Nthe details inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.98,0:14:18.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must say, I'm amazed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.52,0:14:22.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In five days, you found the errand\Nrunner mentioned in the reports...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.02,0:14:25.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and in three days, you've\Nmanaged to gain his complete trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.79,0:14:30.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It takes more to be a Hunter\Nthan being a skilled warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.90,0:14:34.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, our true strength\Nis intelligence-gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:36.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.71,0:14:39.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We now know that the bodyguard...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.38,0:14:42.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...cannot live in Kosenkyo\Nwith Prince Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.21,0:14:45.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...without the assistance\Nof the errand runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.81,0:14:47.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what next?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.02,0:14:50.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that she will\Ncome here in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:55.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stand back and watch,\Nand all will be resolved soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:05.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the deadline is in seven days,\NI'll be able to deliver it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.67,0:15:07.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will this be enough for the deposit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.07,0:15:10.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More than enough! Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:14.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait here a moment.\NI'll go make out your bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.32,0:15:22.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.56,0:16:03.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.33,0:16:11.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oops!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.97,0:16:15.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting.\NHere's your bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.04,0:16:20.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then. I'll deliver the items\Nyou requested in seven days' time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.74,0:16:22.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.48,0:16:25.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.17,0:16:46.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You memorized everything\Nin such a short time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.71,0:17:01.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the distance, I'd estimate\Ntwo days each way if we take our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.72,0:17:03.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Say, five days total.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.66,0:17:09.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure this will last...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.40,0:17:16.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, we're going\Nto Ogi no Shimo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.37,0:17:19.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to pick up money for the trip...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.77,0:17:22.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and I'll get you some\Nleggings and a karru.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.84,0:17:24.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.34,0:17:29.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rai. Hyok.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.18,0:17:30.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rai. Hyok.\NSir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.28,0:17:31.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Taga. Sune.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.21,0:17:31.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Taga. Sune.\NSir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.38,0:17:35.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Split into two-man teams and check\Neach of these locations in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.18,0:17:36.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.02,0:17:38.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you locate the\Nspear-wielder's hideout...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.19,0:17:41.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...make certain you leave one man as\Na lookout and report back immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:43.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll launch a surprise\Nattack as a team.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.49,0:17:47.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Under no circumstances is\Nanyone to engage her alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.66,0:17:49.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will kill her for certain this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.97,0:17:50.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.87,0:17:54.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else, remain here and\Nkeep watch on the errand runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.21,0:18:00.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have nothing to add.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.81,0:18:04.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will leave the searching\Nto you, but I ask that you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.08,0:18:07.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...allow me to accompany you\Nwhen you recover the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.02,0:18:10.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you tried to assassinate him,\Nthe prince got a look at your faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.82,0:18:14.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I am not there,\Nhe will be frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.52,0:18:18.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are not the only one who\Nis concerned about His Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.16,0:18:19.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.46,0:18:24.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. But what\Nabout you, Master Shuga?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.67,0:18:28.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We might locate the\Nspear-wielder's hideout today...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.57,0:18:30.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...or it might be\Nthree days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:32.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As for me, I will\Nreturn to the palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.37,0:18:35.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and prepare for further\Nreading of the epitaphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.91,0:18:40.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as Prince Chagum arrives,\NI must stage his miraculous return...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.62,0:18:44.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and we must also provide\Na state funeral for Prince Sagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:49.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...whose death we have not yet\Nbeen able to disclose to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.39,0:18:51.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To do so, a cover story\Nwill be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.86,0:18:56.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If circumstances warrant it, we may\Nhave to rewrite the official history itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.90,0:19:01.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. We will\Nbe sure to send for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:03.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:39.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How much farther is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:41.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll understand\Nwhen we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.49,0:19:56.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The errand runner\Nis leaving his store.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.83,0:20:00.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.00,0:20:01.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.03,0:20:06.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The boy has never left his shop\Nto deliver goods himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.67,0:20:07.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.27,0:20:08.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yun!\NSir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.87,0:20:13.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Zen, you are to tail him at a distance.\NYour face is known to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.78,0:20:17.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In case of emergency, however,\Nextract information as the "Chief."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.71,0:20:18.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.02,0:20:26.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.32,0:20:29.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, a graveyard.\NCome with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.34,0:20:49.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's this one if I recall correctly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.62,0:20:58.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, what are you doing?\NYou'll get into trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.87,0:21:13.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's too risky to\Nkeep it in the house...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.30,0:21:16.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and carrying it around\Nwould be troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.57,0:21:19.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have it hidden in\Nvarious places, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:21.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Money?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.01,0:21:25.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've been able to live without\Nme working as a bodyguard...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.61,0:21:27.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...because of these secret hoards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.28,0:21:29.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.62,0:21:31.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like a wood shrike's stash.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.25,0:21:35.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wood shrike?\NAh, yes, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.06,0:21:36.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have a way with words.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.37,0:21:46.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be quite a long journey\Nto reach Toumi village.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.64,0:21:49.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Be ready to do a lot of walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:52.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With a new pair of leggings\Nand karru, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.04,0:21:56.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not so sure... I'm not going to\Ncarry you on my back any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.38,0:21:59.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.72,0:22:09.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.13,0:22:12.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take this to buy yourself\Nsome hekimooms or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.59,0:22:14.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.53,0:22:17.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. This will be your last\Nchance to eat them for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.70,0:22:20.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haggle the vendor\Nfor as many as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.67,0:22:21.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.71,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.81,0:24:45.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Having fallen into the Hunters' trap...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.35,0:24:49.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Toya risks his life\Nto rescue Balsa, but then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.05,0:24:52.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time,\N"The Water Mill Burns."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 17\NThe Water Mill Burns
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:54.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Toya.
